,{"awesomeListRepo":"bolshchikov/js-must-watch","categoryHTML":"<h2>2016</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.oreilly.com/ideas/brendan-eich-javascript-fluent-2016\">Brendan Eich: <strong>JavaScript in 2016: Beyond Harmony</strong></a> [15:31]</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-12T10:30:40.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"markets/awesome-ruby","categoryHTML":"<h2>Third-party APIs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/kciter/simple-slack-bot\">simple-slack-bot</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/kciter/simple-slack-bot\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">157</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":157,\"repo\":\"kciter/simple-slack-bot\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - You can easily make Slack Bot.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-12T10:12:04.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"prakhar1989/awesome-courses","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2><h3>Computer Graphics</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ut-cs378-vision-2014fall/course-info\">CS 378</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ut-cs378-vision-2014fall/course-info\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">75</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":75,\"repo\":\"ut-cs378-vision-2014fall/course-info\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> <strong>3D Reconstruction with Computer Vision</strong> <em>UTexas</em> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4bb.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Assignments\" title=\"Assignments\"> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4dd.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Lecture Notes\" title=\"Lecture Notes\">\n<ul>\n<li>In this lab-based class, we'll dive into practical applications of 3D reconstruction, combining hardware and software to build our own 3D environments from scratch. We'll use open-source frameworks like OpenCV to do the heavy lifting, with the focus on understanding and applying state-of-the art approaches to geometric computer vision</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ut-cs378-vision-2014fall/course-info/tree/master/meeting-notes\">Lectures</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-12T06:39:18.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"prakhar1989/awesome-courses","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2><h3>Computer Graphics</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.cornell.edu/Courses/CS4620/2014fa/index.shtml#\">CS 4620</a> <strong>Introduction to Computer Graphics</strong> <em>Cornell University</em> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4bb.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Assignments\"> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4dd.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Lecture Notes\"> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4da.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Readings\">\n<ul>\n<li>The study of creating, manipulating, and using visual images in the computer.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.cornell.edu/Courses/CS4620/2014fa/index.shtml#asgn\">Assignments</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.cornell.edu/Courses/CS4620/2014fa/index.shtml#exams\">Exams</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-12T06:39:18.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"prakhar1989/awesome-courses","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2><h3>Computer Graphics</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.cornell.edu/courses/CS4670/2015sp/\">CS 4670</a> <strong>Introduction to Computer Vision</strong> <em>Cornell University</em> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4bb.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Assignments\" title=\"Assignments\"> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4dd.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Lecture Notes\" title=\"Lecture Notes\"> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4da.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Readings\" title=\"Readings\">\n<ul>\n<li>This course will provide an introduction to computer vision, with topics including image formation, feature detection, motion estimation, image mosaics, 3D shape reconstruction, and object and face detection and recognition. Applications of these techniques include building 3D maps, creating virtual characters, organizing photo and video databases, human computer interaction, video surveillance, automatic vehicle navigation, and mobile computer vision. This is a project-based course, in which you will implement several computer vision algorithms throughout the semester.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.cornell.edu/courses/CS4670/2015sp/projects/projects.html\">Assignments</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.cornell.edu/courses/CS4670/2015sp/lectures/lectures.html\">Lectures</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-12T06:39:18.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"prakhar1989/awesome-courses","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2><h3>Computer Graphics</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://canvas.instructure.com/courses/904706\">CS 6670</a> <strong>Computer Vision</strong> <em>Cornell University</em> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4bb.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Assignments\" title=\"Assignments\"> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4dd.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Lecture Notes\" title=\"Lecture Notes\">\n<ul>\n<li>Introduction to computer vision. Topics include edge detection, image segmentation, stereopsis, motion and optical flow, image mosaics, 3D shape reconstruction, and object recognition. Students are required to implement several of the algorithms covered in the course and complete a final project.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://canvas.instructure.com/courses/904706/assignments/syllabus\">Syllabus</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://canvas.instructure.com/courses/904706\">Lectures</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://canvas.instructure.com/courses/904706/assignments\">Assignments</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-12T06:39:18.000Z"}]}},"pageContext":{"type":"day","from":1457740800000,"to":1457827199999,"previousId":"2016-03-13","nextId":"2016-03-11","nextName":"Mar 11th, 2016","previousName":"Mar 13th, 2016"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","3289010534"]}